<div id="review_1419770161" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1419770161" />
    <a title="Eric" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2170186-eric"><img alt="Eric" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1450267589p2/2170186.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1419770161?book_show_action=true">Oct 18, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eric" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eric" href="/user/show/2170186-eric">Eric</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1419770161" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9132545723998824999">I read this book without reading the first 2 books featuring Roger the Chapman. I did feel that this worked fine as a standalone novel though. I will admit it took me a couple of tries to get through the book because the writing style just isn&apos;t what I typically read. Once I got into however, I had no problem devouring it. <br/>I enjoy the character of Roger and will keep an eye out for more of the books in the future. I kind of saw him as a medieval Sherlock Holmes. The author did well creating the </span>
  <span id="freeText9132545723998824999" style="display:none">I read this book without reading the first 2 books featuring Roger the Chapman. I did feel that this worked fine as a standalone novel though. I will admit it took me a couple of tries to get through the book because the writing style just isn't what I typically read. Once I got into however, I had no problem devouring it. <br />I enjoy the character of Roger and will keep an eye out for more of the books in the future. I kind of saw him as a medieval Sherlock Holmes. The author did well creating the world and keeping events and characters true to the time period. The inconsistency I have found in many books set in this period is that while they keep the obvious things like technology true to the era, they fail to realize that societal interaction and culture was different as well. I felt the author did well avoiding that pitfall.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9132545723998824999" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


