        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer199614576" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14611577016418819245">These medieval mysteries show life the way it probably was during the early middle ages in England. The clever &quot;detective&quot; is a chapman, a skilled peddler and mender of all things who travels from town to town. This episode begins when he stumbles with fever and ends up in the arms of a weaver&apos;s daughter--and has to unravel the mystery of the weaver&apos;s death. The puzzle is engaging, and the characters will involve the reader. The book&apos;s a bit PG 13, with an only marginally positive ending.</span>
  <span id="freeText14611577016418819245" style="display:none">These medieval mysteries show life the way it probably was during the early middle ages in England. The clever "detective" is a chapman, a skilled peddler and mender of all things who travels from town to town. This episode begins when he stumbles with fever and ends up in the arms of a weaver's daughter--and has to unravel the mystery of the weaver's death. The puzzle is engaging, and the characters will involve the reader. The book's a bit PG 13, with an only marginally positive ending.</span>
